parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine valve cover can cause smoke to come from the vents, potentially leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Smoke coming from the vents
unusual noises or smells from the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked cylinder head can cause coolant to leak internally into the engine cylinders, leading to engine damage, overheating, and potentially causing a loss of control or stalling.
symptoms: Coolant leakage
engine overheating
reduced engine performance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Faulty lifters can cause loud ticking noises, which can be a sign of a more serious engine problem, potentially leading to engine damage or failure.
symptoms: Loud ticking noise from the engine
especially when cold.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water pump failure can cause engine overheating, leading to reduced engine performance, damage, or failure.
symptoms: Engine overheating
coolant leakage
reduced engine performance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unusual engine noises can be a sign of a more serious engine problem, potentially leading to engine damage or failure.
symptoms: Tapping or knocking noise from the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause a loss of braking effectiveness, leading to accidents or near-misses, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop or slow down
the brakes make a grinding noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent brake noise can be a sign of worn-out brake pads or shoes, which can lead to a loss of braking effectiveness, causing accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brakes make a grinding noise
the brakes make a squealing noise
the brakes vibrate when applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can cause a loss of braking effectiveness, leading to accidents or near-misses, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop or slow down
the ABS light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can result in serious injuries or fatalities, as the vehicle's occupants are not adequately protected.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
resulting in injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The aggressive deployment of airbags can cause injuries, such as whiplash, facial trauma, and respiratory problems, even in low-speed collisions.
symptoms: Airbags deploy violently
causing whiplash
facial injuries
and respiratory problems.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended deployment of airbags can cause unexpected injuries, distractions, and accidents, and can also lead to vehicle damage and repair costs.
symptoms: Airbags deploy without a crash or collision
causing unexpected injuries and distractions.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Failure to Engage Reverse Gear
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission to engage reverse gear can cause the vehicle to become stuck, increasing the risk of accidents or collisions, especially when reversing out of a driveway or parking space.
symptoms: The vehicle refuses to move in reverse
the transmission fails to engage reverse gear
the vehicle is stuck in a forward gear
the transmission makes unusual noises or vibrations when attempting to shift into reverse.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission to shift gears can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become stuck, increasing the risk of accidents or collisions.
symptoms: The transmission fails to shift gears
the vehicle hesitates or refuses to accelerate
the transmission makes unusual noises or vibrations
the vehicle stalls or loses power.
